==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Yaupon
<hw>Yau"pon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
shrub (<spn>Ilex Cassine</spn>) of the Holly family, native from
Virginia to Florida. The smooth elliptical leaves are used as a
substitute for tea, and were formerly used in preparing the <prod>black
drink</prod> of the Indians of North Carolina. Called also
<altname>South-Sea tea</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>yapon</asp>, <asp>youpon</asp>, and <asp>yupon</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yautia</ent>⟦br⟧
